es are typically much shorter than the jittering\ntimescale. While a jitter of a single reference source can be up to dozens of\n$\\mu as$ over some reasonable observational time, using a sample of reference\nsources would reduce the error in relative astrometry. The obtained results can\nbe used for estimating the physical upper limits on the time-dependent accuracy\nof astrometric measurements.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2017 19:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-03"}
