s clearly demonstrate that sparse\nreconstruction is a useful choice for high-fidelity full-polarimetric\ninterferometric imaging.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2017 19:26:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Feb 2017 23:35:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 3 Mar 2017 18:13:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-29"}
