itial mass of the star could be twice as large as previously estimated\n(nearly ~60 MSun). Reanalysis of the earlier outburst data shows that the peak\nluminosity and outflow velocity of the eruption are consistent with a trend\nexhibited by stellar merger candidates, prompting speculation that SN Hunt248\nmay also have stemmed from a massive stellar merger or common-envelope\nejection.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2017 19:39:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 16 Oct 2017 21:05:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-06"}
