{"id":"1702.00563","submitter":"Thomas Rey","authors":"Ward Melis, Thomas Rey (RAPSODI), Giovanni Samaey","title":"Projective integration for nonlinear BGK kinetic equations","comments":"Proceedings FVCA 8","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NA math.AP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We present a high-order, fully explicit, asymptotic-preserving projective\nintegration scheme for the nonlinear BGK equation. The method first takes a few\nsmall (inner) steps with a simple, explicit method (such as direct forward\nEuler) to damp out the stiff components of the solution. Then, the time\nderivative is estimated and used in an (outer) Runge-Kutta method of arbitrary\norder. Based on the spectrum of the linearized BGK operator, we deduce that,\nwith an appropriate choice of inner step size, the time step restriction on the\nouter time step as well as the number of inner time steps is independent of the\nstiffness of the BGK source term. We illustrate the method with numerical\nresults in one and two spatial dimensions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Feb 2017 07:44:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-03"}
